##"closed city" , he received a lot of people with AIDS for help

The papernews

The function introduction, has the connotation the current politics new media

Intern, Liu Xu, _ paper _ journalist, Yu Yan

Drug withdrawal, what does it mean for people infected with HIV?

He told The Paper that his life could be in danger. AIDS must be taken daily to curb the number of viruses in the body, "once the drug, the virus will rebound, decreased immunity, the risk of infection greatly increased. "

Wuhan "closed city" , he received a lot of AIDS patients for help. These infected persons are at risk of drug withdrawal because they lack access permits and are unable to obtain medicines from designated hospitals.

"The news on the mobile phone is like an explosion. " Huang Yi is the initiator of Wuhan Weixian Social Work Service Center (hereinafter referred to as "Weixian social worker") , a public welfare organization for the prevention and treatment of AIDS.

"Why not ask the community or the village committee for help in getting the medicine? "

"Some people with HIV don't want to identify themselves even when they are off their medication. "

More than 6,300 bottles of drugs were sent: 3,000 HIV infected people were registered in just one hospital

On February 19, the Joint United Nations Programme on HIV/AIDS and the AIDS Public Welfare Organization "Bai Hualin National Alliance" , supported by the China STD and AIDS prevention and Control Center, designed and launched a survey of people living with HIV under the new crown pneumonia.

The survey showed that nearly one-third of the 32.6 percent of people living with HIV / AIDS due to the "city closure" control, in the next few days there may be drug withdrawal; nearly half of those living with HIV / AIDS 48.6 percent said, i don't know where to get my next retrovirus.

Bai Hua, founder and head of the National Union of White Birch forests, told The Paper news on February 25 that the country is usually "localized management" of AIDS patients, that is, where the establishment of a file where regular drug collection. Under the epidemic situation, on January 26, the Chinese Center for Disease Control and Prevention issued a notice on guaranteeing free anti-virus drugs for people living with HIV in other places. Those who are unable to return to their original treatment facilities may temporarily receive free antiviral treatment at the place of detention, the notice said.

Although the CDC and other relevant departments timely awareness of the concerns of infected people, but the drug is still very difficult.

Bai Hua reflects, take medicine need ID card, antiviral treatment number and original treatment center to provide the "work contact letter" . But with the Spring Festival and the prevention and control of the epidemic, some basic-level Centers for Disease Control and prevention could not get through by telephone, and some infected people could not remember their treatment numbers, "I couldn't get through on the phone, [ people ] couldn't get out, and they were all in a hurry. And the holidays had been extended, and some centers and hospitals weren't working yet, but patients were out of medicine. "

Therefore, during the epidemic, the "White Birch Forest National Union" and "for the first social workers" and other public welfare organizations, have issued a drug for patients who are on the verge of or have been out of medicine mailing news.

The National Union of Birch forests, which has worked in the field of AIDS prevention and control for many years, has built up a huge network of patients. In addition to sending out drugs previously stored to infected people by mail, they also set up a bridge of mutual help between the patients who "keep medicine" and those who "do not keep medicine" . More than one thousand, eight hundred people have sought help from the Birchwood National Union, which has distributed drugs to more than 600 of them. "We usually stock up on drugs to help people who are going off their meds in different places, but the amount of medication that people are looking for is not in the same order of magnitude as before, " Betula Platyphylla said.

"Weixian Social Worker" contacted Wuhan Jinyintan Hospital and posted a help antiviral drug form on public accounts and microblogs. It can mail drugs to up to 65 infected people a day. As of March 2, "Weixian social workers" had mailed more than 6,300 bottles of medicine to 741 infected people, but there were 3,000 registered in a single hospital in Jinyintan... They have a lot of work to do...

Afraid to explain the situation to the village committee, walk more than 10 miles to express delivery point to pick up medicine

Zhang Jie, 45, who has been infected for more than three years, was among those seeking help from the National Union of Birch forests in Jingzhou, Hubei Province. Since the diagnosis, daily medication has been a part of Zhang Jie's life. At first he set an alarm to remind him to take his medicine every day, but now it's a habit and he doesn't need it anymore.

Zhang Jie's infection is not known to his parents or other relatives or friends. If asked, he would say he was taking a liver-protecting drug or a liver-protecting supplement. "If he knew, he would not dare to eat with you. ".

On January 21, Zhang Jie, who works in Dongguan, returned to Jingzhou for the Lunar New Year holiday, intending to stay at home for only six or seven days. But with news of the outbreak and the closure of the city, Zhang Jie realized he might not have enough medicine with him. Immediately, Zhang Jie contacted birch. Understanding the situation, Birch sent him by volunteer donations of "Tirai" , three drugs each 15, can eat 15 days.

Zhang Jie, "Telai" is an AIDS patients often eat a combination of three drugs, in addition to "Telai" , "Zilai" and other combinations. The patient of different condition, have different medicaments to mix eat a way. This combination of drugs can greatly reduce the risk of drug resistance in infected people. It is also known as "cocktail therapy" because it is similar to making cocktails with different styles of alcohol.

Although Zhang Jie usually eat "TIRANAI" rather than "Tirai" , but in this case there is no way, "there is better than no.

With two days left in the supply of medicine that Zhang Jie had brought home, the first aid arrived. Zhang Jie, who lives in the countryside, did not dare to explain the situation to the village committee, so he had to walk more than ten miles to the express delivery point to pick up medicine, "In the village, if only one person knew, they would know everything. I was afraid of people looking at me differently. "

Like Zhang Jie, another infected person, Lu Shu, 26, has been infected with HIV for just eight months. With the block block and traffic control in Wuhan further upgrade, unable to get medicine he felt a little flustered. He said that people in the community could help to get the medicine, but he was not in a good position to talk to the community..

"For the first social workers, " said Huang Yi, Hubei has more than 20,000 people infected with AIDS, such a situation is not in the minority, people's prejudice to HIV infected even if they want to hide their identity.

Another "for the first social worker" Staff Xiao Chao observed that AIDS infected with this "stigma" in the elderly is particularly obvious, coupled with unfamiliar with the network, they are more likely to drug withdrawal.

The first few weeks of "first social workers" to seek help for most of the younger people infected with AIDS, until the last week over the age of 50 infected people gradually up. Xiao Chao told the paper that many elderly people do not use smartphones, do not seek help from channels, do not dare to ask for help from neighbors. It was only recently that the hospital voluntarily called the past to ask, and they learned that volunteers could help get medicine.

"A 56-year-old infected person even walked nearly 10 hours overnight to get medicine at the hospital... " Xiao blamed himself for the incident. "If we had seen him earlier, he might not have had to walk so hard. "

"I hear that ring, I want to smash my phone. "

In 2010, when Huang Yi volunteered in the student community, he was exposed to the knowledge of AIDS prevention and treatment, the sense of achievement of this job led him to choose to create the first social worker, for nine years. "They are so stigmatized by society that if someone can help them, it is the only way for them to survive. "

Huang told thepaper.cn that in order to better protect patients' privacy, the volunteers participating in this voluntary service are all their "core members. " There are 22 volunteers online and offline. Each volunteer has to sign a confidentiality agreement, to make sure that the patient's privacy is protected. We have a clear division of Labor, some responsible for the statistics and collation of online help registration form; some responsible for driving the delivery of drugs; some responsible for the hospital drug..

In this voluntary work, Xiao Chao is responsible for answering questions and registering information. In the early days, he had to answer about 70 phone calls a day, while constantly answering questions on Wechat to calm his mood. "They may be pestering you 24 hours a day from the moment they call. " Xiao Chao felt helpless, he spent almost every day on the phone, answering calls, answering messages. But every time he got a little annoyed, he felt sad to hear the infected people tell their stories.

Including his volunteer experience as a student, Xiao Chao, 25, has been working as a "first social worker" for four years. As a sexual minority, he knows that society does not accept this community, "want to do something for this community, want to bring about some change through their own efforts, " Xiao Chao said with some emotion.

However, the anxiety of the infected also affected Xiao, who began losing sleep all night, lost his appetite to eat, and was even afraid to hear the phone ring, "hear that ring and want to smash the phone. ". Later, the team invited psychological counseling, each week will give the volunteers to ease the mood, Xiao Chao also in the team's request for a day off. Now he has slowly adjusted, listening to ballads to calm himself down when he's feeling anxious.

The passport you've always wanted

In addition to the volunteers' emotional well-being, the "pass" was also a big issue.

On the afternoon of the 25th, the car carrying the volunteers was stopped at a bridge in Han River for not having a pass.

"was questioned for nearly half an hour" , Huang Yi and the volunteers feel some injustice.

Huang told thepaper.cn that they have been trying to resolve the issue of the pass, but the social workers'organization is not qualified to issue the pass, and the CDC and hospitals are unable to issue passes to volunteers who do not belong to their units. As a result, the volunteers have been using an "unofficial passport" from the CDC and the hospital -- a stamped fact sheet.

The next day, instead of driving, the volunteers cycled off the medicines that had not been mailed the day before.

Shen Qing is waiting for drugs, infected with AIDS for three years, that the volunteers were stopped after the car, he felt helpless. "The volunteers at the hospital were in the hospital for eight hours, and I saw pictures of people wearing suits that were torn... they were really great. "

"I don't want volunteers to do this in my heart. I hope the relevant departments can take it seriously and solve it, instead of relying on volunteers to rush ahead, " Shen said

In order to get the medicine as soon as possible, Shen Qin called the Wuhan Government Affairs Service Network and the Wuhan Mayor Hotline. Telephone that end, the staff attitude is very good, only said has recorded Shen Qin's request, but still did not tell him the solution, Shen Qin complex mood.

A staff member at the Jiang'an District Center for Disease Control and Prevention in Wuhan told The Paper news that most people in the unit are now involved in work related to new pneumonia. As for work related to AIDS, the main task is to contact hospitals for local infected people, provide "work contact letter" to the infected people in the field to help them get the medicine and so on.

At this point, Birch understands the authorities. White Birch heard that in Anhui, Zhejiang, some of the lighter epidemic, the number of people infected with AIDS in a small number of places have a disease control drive drug delivery. But for more places, Bai believes that this way of working is not feasible, "everyone is so busy, the workload is so big, if they one by one to deliver medicine, it is almost impossible. "

However, the turnaround for Weixian social worker came quickly. On the afternoon of the 26th, Huang sent a letter to Wechat, and they got a pass.

On the night the volunteer car was stopped, Huang posted a message on his Weibo Account, which received more than 10 million views. The next day many departments contacted Huang, "community, hospital, Civil Affairs, Youth League Committee, Disease Control, traffic control, health and so on, many units have given us very big support and help. "

Finally, under the guidance of the relevant departments, at noon on the 26th, he submitted his application to the Civil Affairs Bureau of Wuchang District, the administrative unit of Xianshe. At 5:30 pm, the volunteers finally got their coveted passes, they can continue to drive and deliver the medicine.

(Huang Yi, Shen Qing, Zhang Jie and Lu Shu are all pseudonyms)
